data.text:
Erica Kane, Transaction Manager

Office: (801) 225-7272

Cell: (801) 347-6149

Email: erica.krugergroup@gmail.com

Erica was born and raised in Utah County. She attended Pleasant Grove High School where she cheered, played Volleyball, and was on the Events Committee of Student Council. She earned a scholarship to the University of Utah where she attended college. While attending the U, Erica studied business finance. She later used that to work at a Credit Union for 4+ years helping people with their finances, banking, and loans.

Erica is the Transaction Coordinator for the Kruger Real Estate Group. She has been working in the Real Estate Industry since the young age of 20 years old. She even bought her first home at age 20! As the transaction coordinator, she does a lot of the behind the scenes work. Erica also helps motivate the agents and keep them organized. She loves helping clients make the process of selling or buying a home as smooth as possible! In her free time Erica is usually outdoors often doing fun activities such as hiking, boating, skiing, health/fitness, with her husband Jacob and family.
